txt.en: 'Let this be known to your people, Azruthor... the Dead do not suffer the living!'
'The Scourge yet lives and may the bloodline never be broken! Balakh√¥r shall bring you all to ruin!'
'No! You cannot abandon me now! The Dark Lord shall hear of this....'
'Were you cursed like me, I would think it true, but I do not believe he shall hear anything of you....'
'I curse you again - all of you and your treacherous folk! None defy the servants of Sauron and live!'
'Who dares challenge the Dead?'
'Not YOU again! You shall suffer my fear yet, [placeholder]!'
'You shall never purge the Dead from these lands....'
'There is only death for you here, [placeholder].'
'Let dread consume you!'
'I have been failed by the Dead, and then failed by my men - all because of you, [placeholder].'
'All this time you have thought us fools, Azruthor.'
'You have meddled in the affairs of the true King of Gondor for too long, and I will not fail the Scourge now!'
'We have seen much of this world, and shall evermore - cursed as we are.'
'The only escape you shall find now is death!'
'When we sought to spite the heir of Isildur, we swore allegiance to Sauron the Great, not a miserable Man such as you.'
'If your plan was to leave me defenceless, you have failed!'
'You are no stronger than any other Living, and are no more deserving of our service than Isildur's heir.'
'We shall travel east and serve our Lord, Sauron. For he alone shall command us to victory....'
'Fools! Not only the living serve under my command!'
